## Packing it up

The three dots `...` have a dual identity. If used inside a Function Parameter definition, it does the exact REVERSE of Spread. It acts as the **Rest Operator**.

It "gathers up the rest" of the randomly provided arguments and packs them tightly into an Array!

```javascript
// It will pack all remaining arguments into a 'numbers' array!
function printNumbers(a, b, ...numbers) {
  console.log(numbers);
}

// We called it with 5 arguments.
printNumbers("First", "Second", 3, 4, 5);
// Outputs: [ 3, 4, 5 ]
```
